.\" termin.al-name: login
.\" termin.al-usage: login
.\" termin.al-summary: Authenticate with GitHub.
.TH LOGIN 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
login \- Authenticate with GitHub.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
login
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Names the future authentication entry point. Authentication is intentionally unavailable in the current public application.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ login
.fi
.SH NOTES
The command currently returns a stable unavailable-feature diagnostic and does not begin an authentication flow.
.SH SEE ALSO
help(1), man(1)
